The following article delves into the intricate and often brutal history of the global [animal fur](/Animal_fur) trade. If you're expecting a heartwarming tale of human-animal cooperation, you've clearly misunderstood the nature of both species. This isn't a story of mutual respect, but rather one of relentless pursuit, economic opportunism, and the enduring human penchant for adornment, regardless of the cost. The facts, as presented, are as stark as a winter landscape, much like the terrain that yielded so much of this "soft gold."

"Fur Trade" redirects here. For the band, see [Fur Trade (band)](/Fur_Trade_(band)).

